<typeStatus box="[1013,1059,1664,1688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="383">type</typeStatus>
host plant, gender feminine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1459,485,1792]" pageId="3" pageNumber="383">
Remarks. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hong &amp; Kuang, 1989" authorityName="Hong &amp; Kuang" authorityYear="1989" box="[618,1018,1698,1723]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Leipothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lysimachiae">
<emphasis box="[618,774,1698,1722]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="383">L. lysimachiae</emphasis>
Hong 
<emphasis box="[849,870,1698,1721]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="383">&amp;</emphasis>
Kuang, 1989
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the complete prodorsal shield median line, absent submedian lines, and absent setae 
<emphasis box="[1089,1115,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="383">h1</emphasis>
. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hong &amp; Kuang" authorityYear="1989" box="[1160,1317,1733,1757]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Leipothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lysimachiae">
<emphasis box="[1160,1317,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="383">L. lysimachiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the median and submedian lines are incomplete and setae 
<emphasis box="[630,657,1767,1791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="383">h1</emphasis>
is present (Hong &amp; Kuang, 1989).
</paragraph>
